        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 6:43PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Lake Minatare State Recreation Area, or 12 miles
northeast of Scottsbluff, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flahertys Corner, Lake Alice, Lake Minatare State Recreation Area,
Lake Alice Number 2, and Kilpatrick Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for the Panhandle
of Nebraska.</instruction>
